Source: psc-pydev
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: P. S. Clarke <debs@pscl4rke.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>=9)
Standards-Version: 3.9.6

Package: psc-pydev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, pep8, pyflakes, python2.7, python2.7-doc,
 python-nose, python-pip, python-virtualenv, virtualenvwrapper,
Description: Collecton of packages for Python development
 This metapackage provides nothing itself, but depends on lots of
 packages that the maintainer uses when working in Python
 .
   * pep8 - a style checker
   * pyflakes - static analysis
   * python2.7 - an actual interpreter
   * python-nose - a common test runner
   * python-pip - to acquire libraries
   * python-virtualenv - isolate dependencies
   * virtualenvwrapper - makes virtualenv usable
 .
 Their documentation is also included.
